<br>
(Also, ALL emphasis is mine in any of the verses I use.)<br>
<br>
&quot;But the Lord abides forever;<br>
He has established His throne for judgement,<br>
And He will judge the world in righteousness;<br>
[snip]<br>
And those who know Thy name will put their trust in Thee;<br>
For Thou, O Lord, has not forsaken those who seek Thee.&quot;<br>
~Psalm 9: 7-10<br>
<br>
&quot;How blessed is he whose transgression is forgiven,<br>
Whose sin is covered!<br>
How blessed is the man to whom the Lord does not impute iniquity&quot;<br>
~Psalm 32: 1<br>
<br>
&quot;As far as the east if from the west,<br>
So far has He removed our transgressions from us.&quot;<br>
~Psalm 103: 12 <br>
<br>
I could go on and on how David realized and wrote about how strong God's love is for us. He alone is our Salvation. He promises to never forsake us.<br>
<br>
John wrote:<br>
<br>
&quot;And the witness is this, that God has given us ETERNAL LIFE, and this life is in His Son.<br>
These things I have written to you who believe in the name of the Son of God in order that you may KNOW that you have ETERNAL LIFE.<br>
And this is the confidence which we have before Him, that, if we ask anything according to His will, He hears us&quot;<br>
~1 John 5: 11-14<br>
<br>
That we may KNOW.. that's key. We don't have to wonder, we don't have to worry, no guessing, we KNOW. Jesus give us ETERNAL LIFE. <br>
<br>
John also said:<br>
<br>
&quot;My sheep hear my voice, and I know them and they follow Me;<br>
And I give ETERNAL LIFE to them; and they shall never perish, and NO ONE shall snatch them out of My hand.<br>
My Father, who has given them to Me is greater than all; and no one is able to snatch them out of the Father's hand&quot;<br>
~John 10: 27-29<br>
<br>
Which if a wondeful follow up to <br>
<br>
&quot;Behold I have inscribed you on the palms of My hands.&quot;<br>
~Isaiah 49: 16<br>
<br>
NO one, NOTHING can take us from God once we are His. Romans makes this quite clear<br>
<br>
&quot;For I am convinced that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor principialities nor things present, nor things to come, nor powers,<br>
nor height, nor depth, nor any other created thing, shall be able to separate us from the love of God, which is in Christ Jesus&quot;<br>
~Romans 8: 38-39<br>
<br>
That would include US. WE are not stronger than God. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=t0mmyt>T0mmyT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style=color:green;><b>Mead Master<br>of the Grand Hooley<br>Cheeky Boy</b></span></span><br>  Posts: 420<br> <font color=#B87333>(11/11/03 5:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 1st Affirmative Statement Rebuttal</span><hr size=1> I agree that we are NOT talking about those who only pretend that they are believers.  Since you used David in your examples, we’ll table the exact phrase of “those that have accepted Jesus as Savior” for the moment.  I also agree that David attested to God’s strong love for us and that God would never forsake us (as I also stated in my Opening Statement) and that He alone is our Salvation.  But God not forsaking us is DIFFERENT than us not forsaking God (as is evident that we have done throughout salvation history)!<br>
<br>
I agree with 1 John 5:11-14 and your stated assessment of it that we may know that Jesus gives us eternal life.  This passage speaks to our moral assurance of salvation but not our personal absolute assurance.  Just to note that while John 10:27-29 does use the words “no one” it does NOT use the word “NOTHING” as you stated.  Nor does it or its context suggest that one does not “lose their salvation” if they grievously sin or fall away.  The beginning of the verse states “they follow Me”.  So while Satan may not snatch a believer away, what happens when those individuals following Him choose to not follow him by committing adultery, murdering, etc?  <br>
<br>
I don’t believe that the verses quoted from Romans speak AT ALL about personal eternal security.  Nowhere does it talk about being safe from your own sin.  All the things listed in those 2 verses and the previous verses are EXTERNAL forces (things over which one has no control) and not INTERNAL forces.  In other words God is a faithful and loving God and He won’t let any external forces disrupt the salvation process, but whether an individual who claims to follow God will continue to be faithful to God is open to question.  In summary both John and Romans are speaking about general security (a moral assurance of salvation) and not individual CERTAINTY.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oneandonlyfemme>One and Only Femme</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style=color:green;><b>Five-Star Drama Queen</b></span></span><br>  Posts: 271<br> <font color=#B87333>(11/15/03 12:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/carpechocolateum/that WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My response to Tommy</span><hr size=1>  [Just to note that while John 10:27-29 does use the words “no one” it does NOT use the word “NOTHING” as you stated.]<br>
<br>
Tommy, the &quot;nothing&quot; was my comment, not stated as scripture. But, it seems reasonable that &quot;nothing&quot; can be taken from &quot;NO ONE&quot;. Also, wouldn't &quot;NO ONE&quot; mean US? We're part of &quot;NO ONE&quot;.<br>
<br>
[what happens when those individuals following Him choose to not follow him by committing adultery, murdering, etc?]<br>
<br>
You mean like David? What did happen to him? He recieved God's judgement, the consequences for his sin, then God's forgiveness.  God doesn't forsake us, He promises to NOT forsake us. <br>
<br>
[I don’t believe that the verses quoted from Romans speak AT ALL about personal eternal security.]<br>
<br>
Why not? It speaks about being separated from God. That would mean our salvation.  <br>
<br>
[In other words God is a faithful and loving God and He won’t let any external forces disrupt the salvation process, but whether an individual who claims to follow God will continue to be faithful to God is open to question.]<br>
<br>
So, man IS stronger than all other beings in the universe? I can't agree. <br>
<br>
Also, God promises to give us strength to over come.<br>
<br>
&quot;No temptation has overtaken you but such as in common to man; and GOD IS FAITHFUL, who will NOT ALLOW you to be tempted BEYOND what you are able' but with the temptation will provide the way of escape also, that you may be able to endure it.&quot;<br>
~1 Cor 10: 13<br>
<br>
God's promise is clear. I go back to:<br>
<br>
&quot;Behold I have inscribed you on the palms of My hands.&quot;<br>
~Isaiah 49: 16<br>
<br>
We are FOREVER tatooed on His palms. He will never let us go. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#B87333>- </font><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth>Sparrow's Hearth</a><font color=#B87333> - </font><a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm21>Tournaments</a> <font color=#B87333> - </font><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth"><font face=verdana size=4>Sparrow's Hearth</font></a><font color=#B87333> - </font> <h1 align=center><a href=http://bible.gospelcom.net/><img src=http://heartjoys.fcpages.com/Sparrow'sHearth/logo_gospelcom.gif></a></h1><p>
